Sentencas: The Y0.07Sr0.93Ti0.8Fe0.2O3.8 (YSTF) material was fabricated using three different synthesis methods: modified polymer precursor method (MPP), Pechini method and a solid state reaction method.
Titulo: The influence of synthesis method on the microstructure and catalytic performance of Y0.07Sr0.93Ti0.8Fe0.2O3-8 in synthetic biogas operated solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: It was applied as an anode catalytic material for biogas reforming in solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: The influence of synthesis method on the microstructure and catalytic performance of Y0.07Sr0.93Ti0.8Fe0.2O3-8 in synthetic biogas operated solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Clear differences in the microstructure of fabricated catalytic layers were found, mainly with respect to a grain size and distribution of grains.
Titulo: The influence of synthesis method on the microstructure and catalytic performance of Y0.07Sr0.93Ti0.8Fe0.2O3-8 in synthetic biogas operated solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: This led to some differences in biogas diffusion through the layer as well as in an amount of active sites for a biogas reforming.
Titulo: The influence of synthesis method on the microstructure and catalytic performance of Y0.07Sr0.93Ti0.8Fe0.2O3-8 in synthetic biogas operated solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Also different chemical stability of each compound was observed in the fuel cell operating conditions.
Titulo: The influence of synthesis method on the microstructure and catalytic performance of Y0.07Sr0.93Ti0.8Fe0.2O3-8 in synthetic biogas operated solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The best long-term stability in biogas was found for a fuel cell with the YSTF_Pechini catalytic layer (sintered in air at 1100 degrees C for 2 h) and the lowest one for a fuel cell with the YSTF_MPP layer.
Titulo: The influence of synthesis method on the microstructure and catalytic performance of Y0.07Sr0.93Ti0.8Fe0.2O3-8 in synthetic biogas operated solid oxide fuel cells
